**Idea:**

We start by sorting both teams in increasing order. For the Navalur team we store the sorted players in a double‐ended queue (deque). Then, we process the Siruseri players (also in increasing order) one by one. For each Siruseri player:


**If** his rating is greater than the rating of the Navalur player at the front of the deque (i.e. the weakest available Navalur), he can win that pairing. We then remove that Navalur player from the front and count this as a win.
**Otherwise**, he cannot beat the weakest remaining Navalur opponent. In that case we “sacrifice” his chance by pairing him with the strongest available Navalur player (at the back of the deque) and remove that player.
This strategy is optimal because it always reserves the lower‐rated Navalur players for Siruseri players who can secure a win, while “wasting” the best Navalur players against those Siruseri players that cannot win any pairing.

